
# Ingredients App ‚Äì Master TODO & Workflow Guide

This guide reorganizes your existing TODO list into **clear phases**, **checkable tasks**, and a **logical build order**. Each item is written so you can delete it as you complete it.

---

## PHASE 1: CORE USER FLOW (MVP PATH)

> Goal: User selects ingredients ‚Üí gets recipes ‚Üí saves meals

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Food Style / Preferences Page

* [ ] Fix **"Confirm your selection"** behavior
* [ ] Ensure selected food styles **stay highlighted** unless deselected
* [ ] Persist food style selections when navigating away

---

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Recipe Search / Generation Page

* [ ] Create loading/searching screen while recipes generate
* [ ] Integrate **Spoonacular API** for recipe fetching
* [ ] Generate **6‚Äì8 identical recipe cards per page**
* [ ] Add **prev / next page buttons** for recipes
* [ ] Add page counter (seen vs unseen pages)

---

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Recipe Results Page (Based on User Inputs)

* [ ] Display meals filtered by:

  * Selected ingredients
  * Food styles
  * Meal type (Breakfast / Lunch / Dinner)
* [ ] Show ingredient match indicator (e.g. ‚Äú8 of 10 ingredients matched‚Äù)
* [ ] Show missing ingredients count
* [ ] Add "I made this" engagement button

---

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Calendar Page

* [ ] Build calendar UI
* [ ] Enable saving recipes to specific dates
* [ ] Make calendar update in real time
* [ ] Add visible **plus (+) button** on hover for each date
* [ ] Allow past dates to retain saved recipes

---

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Favorites / Bookmarks

* [ ] Bookmark recipe from recipe card
* [ ] View all saved recipes on Favorites page
* [ ] Remove recipe from favorites

---

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Home / User Landing Page

* [ ] Create Home page layout
* [ ] Display quick links (Calendar, Favorites, Pantry)
* [ ] Add progress indicator showing where user is in flow

